Redis Adopts Dual Source-Available Licensing | Redis

Redis announced a transition to dual source-available licensing for the Redis core software, using RSALv2 and SSPLv1 from version 7.4 onwards. This change aims to simplify licensing, provide flexibility for developers, and protect the future of Redis as a real-time data platform.

- Redis transitions to dual source-available licensing, using RSALv2 and SSPLv1 from version 7.4 onwards
- The new licensing approach aims to simplify packaging, offer flexibility, and ensure sustainable development
- The change does not affect end users of Redis open-source products or third-party libraries
- Commercial customers of Redis will continue under separately negotiated licensing terms
- Competitive offerings derived from Redis will need commercial licensing terms, impacting providers
- The new license aligns all source-available modules with the core of Redis
- Redis will continue to backport security patches until the release of Redis Community Edition 9.0
